---
import CliPreview from "./cli";
import PageSection from "./pageSection.astro";
---

<PageSection
  className="grid grid-cols-1 xl:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 pb-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:grid lg:gap-x-8 xl:gap-x-12"
  size={"24"}
  id="about"
>
  <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-[800px] flex-col gap-2 md:gap-4 xl:max-w-full">
    <h2
      class="mb-2 w-full text-3xl font-bold text-cos-green-50 md:text-5xl lg:text-5xl"
    >
      Data first, code second.
    </h2>
    <p
      class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-cos-green-200 md:text-xl lg:text-xl xl:text-xl"
    >
      We built CustomerOS to do one thing: Bring all your customer data into
      one place so you can use it to power your business without the fuss.
    </p>
    <p
      class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-cos-green-200 md:text-xl lg:text-xl xl:text-xl"
    >
      After countless projects and many years of rebuilding our data layer,
      we became fed up of building the same data processes and stores time and time again.
    </p>
    <p
      class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-cos-green-200 md:text-xl lg:text-xl xl:text-xl"
    >
      We have made many mistakes, and hopefully you will see the result of our hard
      learnt lessons here. Start with your data, and build your business on top of it.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="min-h-[300px] md:min-h-[400px]">
    <CliPreview client:only="react" />
  </div>
</PageSection>
